// This alignment numbers are the "default" or "base" numbers and
// all others are derived from this.
//
// How to derive another set of alignment numbers:
// We assume:
// - Sprites are aligned by their upper left corner.
// - Vehicle sprites have their wheels at the bottom of the sprite.
// - Vehicle sprites are aligned in the pcx such that the back (if any) is at the border, if
//   they are shorter than the available width (important for engines). Wagons need to be centred.
// Thus:
// - Taller sprites need their y-offset adjusted by the difference to this value here
// - Wider sprites need their x-offset adjusted ONLY for the sprite facing right by the
//   difference in widths (sprites wider than this 32px will anyway glitch)
// - Narrower sprites need their x-offset adjusted ONLY for the sprite facing right.

